window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Judgement is inescapable.</b><br> <b>Only a fool would try to evade it.</b><br> <br> Chesapeake Valley is a charming town hiding many secrets.<br> Sheriff Eve Wicker has spent years trying to unearth one of its dark mysteries.<br> <i>The truth behind her mother’s death.</i><br> After moving back to her hometown, she found herself ensnared in a web of conspiracies,<br> from serial killers to child trafficking networks.<br> <br> When a beloved member of the community, Martha Hawthorne is found dead in her home,<br> the case is quickly ruled as one of natural causes.<br> Months later, Amy Hawthorne, her granddaughter, inherits the Hawthorne home.<br> Not long after her move, she is found dead in a gruesome manner.<br> <br> Prior to Amy’s death, she was being stalked and harassed by the town’s <i>“witch”.</i><br> She even reached out to the town pastor to exorcise the home, after multiple <i>\"supernatural\" </i>occurrences.</p> <p>Hoping to get to the bottom of the Hawthorne case, before the wild theories surrounding their death spread like wildfire,<br> Eve begins to unravel a thread, leading to a great scandal.<br> <br> <b><i>Generations of secrets and lives built upon lies.<br> The sins of the past have cast a shadow over the present.</i></b></p>"; 
